## Icons

- [Bootstrap Icons](https://icons.getbootstrap.com/) by The Bootstrap Authors, MIT. The eyedropper icon (`bi-eyedropper`) is embedded inline as SVG in the preview panel toolbar.

## Lua References

- [wasmoon](https://github.com/ceifa/wasmoon) by Gabriel Francisco, MIT. Lua 5.4 WASM with JS interop.
- [Lua](https://www.lua.org/) by PUC Rio, MIT. Official Lua portable C interpreter. Versions 5.1 (2006; matches WoW) up to 5.5.0 (2026)
- [Fengari](https://github.com/fengari-lua/fengari) by daurnimator and team, MIT. Full Lua 5.3 VM in the browser for javascript interop.

## BLP Decoding

- [js-blp](https://github.com/Kruithne/js-blp) by Kruithne, MIT. BLP texture reader. The palette (encoding=1) decode path in `src/assets/blp-decode.ts` is a TypeScript port of the `_getUncompressed` and `_getAlpha` methods.

## CASC References

- [wow.export](https://github.com/Kruithne/wow.export) by Kruithne, MIT. Javascript GUI for WoW CASC archives in a "batteries included" system.
- [CascLib](https://github.com/ladislav-zezula/CascLib) by Ladislav Zezula, MIT. C Library and a great reference implementation of CASC, BLTE, encoding, manifests, MNDX/MARR, more.
- [SereniaBLPLib](https://github.com/WoW-Tools/SereniaBLPLib) by Xalcon, MIT. C# library for BLP texture parsing and DXT decompression.
- [TACTLib](https://github.com/overtools/TACTLib) by the Overtools team, MIT. C# CASC implementation with good TVFS and static-container implementations.
- [wowdev.wiki](https://wowdev.wiki/CASC) documenting CASC/TACT formats and community listfiles.
- [casc-extractor](https://github.com/Xerrion/casc-extractor) by Xerrion, MIT. Rust CLI and library for WoW CASC archives.
